      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RAMSET READY (4) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 2.5 lengths win at this track in a handy 22.75. Awkwardly drawn but likes the trip. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. SHADOW ASSASSIN (2) hit the ground running last time with a fast early split and never headed, leading throughout to win by 4 lengths (22.82) over 401m at this track. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Can make it two on the bounce. CORLESS DEVIOUS (1) had been racing well prior to his last start sixth at Gosford following a Grade 5 win three back with a second placing. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Key player on best and worth another try. NOIR (3) is a last start winner who rates one of the chances again.",
